    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-07-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="378"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d378">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State.</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-07-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 20, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Questions as to times of payment, currency, and interest are under consideration
                    with Spanish minister here. You will not raise or discuss these points unless
                    expressly instructed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adee</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Memorandum.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <p>The Government of Spain will, on or before the fifteenth day of September
                        next, pay to the United States one million five hundred thousand dollars
                        ($1,500,000) in Spanish gold pesos, in full discharge and satisfaction not
                        only of the principal sum agreed to be paid in liquidation of the Mora
                        claim, so called, but of any and every amount that might be claimed to be
                        due as interest on said principal sum.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <dateline rendition="#left">
                            <placeName>Boston</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1895-08-10">August 10, 1895</date>.</dateline>
                        <lb/>
                        <signed>
                            <list>
                                <item>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney</hi>,<lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State of the United
                                    States</hi>.</item>
                                <item>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Dupuy de Lôme</hi>,<lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Minister from Spain to the United
                                    States</hi>.</item>
                                <item>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">J. I. Rodriguez</hi>,<lb/>(<hi
                                        rend="italic">Counsel and Attorney in Fact for Mr.
                                    Mora</hi>),</item>
                                <item>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. D. Shipman</hi>,<lb/>(<hi rend="italic"
                                        >Of counsel</hi>),<lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Representing Mora and all Persons Interested
                                        in said Mora Claim</hi>.</item>
                            </list>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
